ğŸ“„ 1. docker-compose.yml
yaml
Copy
Edit
version: '3'
services:
  bbConA:
    image: busybox
    container_name: bbConA
    command: sh -c "sleep 3600"
    networks:
      - mynet

  bbConB:
    image: busybox
    container_name: bbConB
    command: sh -c "sleep 3600"
    networks:
      - mynet

networks:
  mynet:
    driver: bridge
sleep 3600 keeps the containers running (for 1 hour) so you can manually exec into them.

âœ… Step 2: Run the Compose File
bash
Copy
Edit
cd busybox-compose
docker-compose up -d
This creates two containers: bbConA and bbConB on a custom bridge network called mynet.

âœ… Step 3: Ping bbConB from bbConA
